Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue has been actively engaging with the agriculture community since he took office. He has visited various locations across the country to meet with farmers and ranchers, expressing the USDA's commitment to serving them. Additionally, Perdue has announced new flexibility for local schools in the school meals program and has shown support for opening up international markets for American products, including U.S. beef. Furthermore, he has visited areas affected by natural disasters and pledged USDA resources to assist those in need. Perdue has also interacted with young farmers from organizations like the Future Farmers of America and 4-H, giving him hope for the future of American agriculture. Overall, his goal is to be a strong advocate for American agriculture and promote the sale of U.S. food and fiber worldwide.